The paper deals with feature selection, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The use of population-based optimization algorithms like PSO and genetic algorithms is also mentioned, which are commonly used in the sub-fields of machine learning and optimization. The paper also proposes a new algorithm for feature selection, which involves the use of an Alternating Decision Tree (ADT) classifier and a modified objective function. These techniques are commonly used in the sub-fields of machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.DM (Data Mining), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
